trMA.AposIdiomelon1.text = "With gladness let us embrace the Fast, O peoples, for the beginning of spiritual struggles has arrived. Let us leave off pampering the flesh, let us increase the spiritual gifts of our souls, let us share in Christ's sufferings, as his servants, that we may also be glorified as children of God, and that when they have established the Holy Spirit dwelling in us, he may enlighten our souls."
trMA.AposMartyric.text = " Christ's warriors scorned the fear of kings and tyrants, and boldly and bravely they confessed him, Lord God and King of all, and they intercede in behalf of our souls."
trMA.AposTheotokion.text = "O Theotokos, protector of all who are in need, in you we are made bold, in you we boast, and in you is all our hope. Intercede with him who was born of you, for your unprofitable servants."
trVE.AposIdiomelon1.text = "Let us hasten, through fasting, to be cleansed of the filth of our sins, and through mercy and acts of kindness to the poor, to enter into the bridal chamber of Christ the bridegroom, who bestows on us great mercy."
trVE.AposMartyric.text = "O Martyrs of the Lord, pray fervently to our God and ask for abundant tender mercies for our souls, and forgiveness for our many falls, we pray."
trVE.AposTheotokion.text = "Let us devoutly praise the glorious and immaculate true Theotokos as the Mother of God, greeting her as did the Angel: Rejoice, holy Mother of the incarnate Son of God, rejoice, dwelling place of the Holy Spirit, always interceding for us, for the salvation of our souls."
